:: Rejection target: a single conditional cluster whose consequent contains
:: both `solid` and `non solid` is a closure-time cluster contradiction.
:: Normalizing or firing the registration would place an attribute and its
:: negation on the same subject, so the checker must emit a fatal cluster
:: diagnostic before publishing any verified closure/export result
:: (doc/spec/en/17.clusters_and_registrations.md, sections 17.4 and 17.7.3;
:: architecture 04 lists contradictory attributes as a registration diagnostic).

definition
  let x be set;
  attr HollowDef: x is hollow means x = x;
  attr SolidDef: x is solid means x = x;
end;

registration
  cluster HollowContradiction: hollow -> solid non solid for set;
  coherence proof thus thesis; end;
end;
